.TH XTGEOIP 1 "" "xtgeoip 2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xtgeoip
	Build and manage xt_geoip data from MaxMind GeoLite2 CSVs.

.SH TOP LEVEL
Legacy top-level flag mode without a subcommand.
.TP
xtgeoip
display usage
Exit status: 1
No arguments prints usage and exits non-zero.
.TP
xtgeoip -h
display usage
Exit status: 0
Explicit help prints usage and exits zero.
.TP
xtgeoip -b
back up binary data in /usr/share/xt_geoip/ using the manifest; store backups in /var/lib/xt_geoip/
.TP
xtgeoip -b -c
back up and clean binary data using the manifest
.TP
xtgeoip -b -c -f
force backup and clean even without a manifest
.TP
xtgeoip -b -f
force backup of binary data in /usr/share/xt_geoip/ even without a manifest
.TP
xtgeoip -b -p
back up binary data in /usr/share/xt_geoip/, then prune old backups in /var/lib/xt_geoip/
.TP
xtgeoip -b -p -f
unsupported option, ambiguous and prune does not support force
.TP
xtgeoip -c
clean (delete) binary data in /usr/share/xt_geoip/ using the manifest
.TP
xtgeoip -c -f
force clean (delete) binary data in /usr/share/xt_geoip/ even without a manifest
.TP
xtgeoip -c -p
unsupported option, clean has no prune function
.TP
xtgeoip -c -p -f
unsupported option combination
.TP
xtgeoip -p
unsupported option combination
.TP
xtgeoip -f
unsupported option, top-level mode without backup or clean does not support force
.TP
xtgeoip -l
unsupported option, -l is not valid for top-level mode
.SH BUILD
Build xt_geoip data from the local CSV copy.
.TP
xtgeoip build
build using local copy of database
.TP
xtgeoip build -l
build using local copy of database in legacy mode
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -p
backup, prune backups, then build
.TP
xtgeoip build -p
unsupported option, build has no prune function
.TP
xtgeoip build -c -f
clean using manifest, then build using local copy of database
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -c -p
backup, prune backups, clean, then build
.TP
xtgeoip build -b -c -p -f
unsupported option, ambiguous and prune does not support force
.SH CONF
Configuration operations.
Usage: xtgeoip conf <FLAG>
.TP
xtgeoip conf
missing required argument, conf requires FLAG
.TP
xtgeoip conf -s
show current config
.TP
xtgeoip conf -d
show default config
.TP
xtgeoip conf -e
edit config
.SH FETCH
Download or refresh the local MaxMind CSV archive set.
.TP
xtgeoip fetch
fetch CSVs
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -p
fetch CSVs, then prune CSV archives
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -l
unsupported option, -l is not valid for fetch
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -b
unsupported option, -b is not valid for fetch
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -c
unsupported option, -c is not valid for fetch
.TP
xtgeoip fetch -f
unsupported option, -f is not valid for fetch
.SH RUN
Fetch, then build, optionally wrapping with backup/clean/prune.
.TP
xtgeoip run
fetch, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -l
fetch, then build in legacy mode
.TP
xtgeoip run -p
fetch, then prune CSV archives, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -p
clean using manifest, then fetch, then prune CSV archives, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -f
force clean without manifest, then fetch, then build
.TP
xtgeoip run -c -p -f
unsupported option, ambiguous and prune does not support force
.TP
xtgeoip run -b -c -p
unsupported option, ambiguous (does prune apply to fetch or backup?)
.SH VERSION
Show the program version.
.TP
xtgeoip -V
display version
